<|startoftext|>Question:How do I ask my girlfriend out? How do I let her know that I'm interested and that I want to be with my girlfriend?
Answer:First, do you know what you have in mind. In other words:  if you are asking her out, then let her know that you love her and want to try out your new home.  Ask her if she has a crush on you.  If she does, maybe a friendship will come first.

If she does, ask if she would like to hang out for dinner.  If she does, and if she doesn't say no, then maybe you two could come up with a plan.

If she doesn't say yes, ask her, ""Do you really like what I'm wearing?""  

If she says ""Yes,"" give her a little ""thank you.""  So she can tell you exactly how you feel.

You can also try the same thing with your girlfriend, if she's really interested in you and wants to try out new homes.  Go into her room and let it start to go.  If she says no, just leave the door so you can go out to dinner if you like.  If she refuses, give it a little time.

If she says yes, and you see what she like to do on the couch, then you can move on to other things.

Good Luck.  It's really, really, really easy for guys to fall in love if they don't think that will do anything for them.  Don't let it make you think about your girlfriend.  It will make you think twice about whether or not you like her for who she is.  If you don't get a chance, ask yourself if this will ever ever happen again.  It really is a tough thing to do, but it's worth it.  Just leave her and move forward.<|endoftext|>
