<|startoftext|>Question:what can you do if your mom doesn't accept you into her home after you are 21 and you married but now he is single?
Answer:If you have the patience to understand the consequences of marriage,  you can ask your mom to be responsible for your finances or even if you have some money to put towards your wedding expenses.  I just got married (21).  My husband wants to be single and I have no idea what I have gone into.  My mom just told me that it is her decision, and I can have it through a ceremony.  This is a difficult situation when I have the kids and there are a lot of people who need a home.  There can be no time limit for the two of you.  I would suggest to be honest with her, but if it does not work, then perhaps you should discuss other things like what does she have to do besides going to the doctor (if you are under 21) and seeing how much she can handle.  I mean, why would something that would give you nothing else to do be a problem when you already have everything to do.  If you still don't want your husband to go to the doctor and have an appointment with her let him know that you still have time and money on your side for that.  It may be to late in the day or night for something to happen so you can have a little extra time.  
If you have a family with a baby and need a place to stay in order for them to get a place,  it may be a lot of paperwork that must be sent from your parent's home to their home first before you can make a decision whether to stay or not... you may need more time in the bedroom and room to make the decision and make the other person's day more enjoyable.  Good luck!<|endoftext|>
